# Next.js Guidelines

## App Router Structure

### Directory Organization
- [src/app/](mdc:src/app) - Main application routes
- [src/app/(protected)/](mdc:src/app/(protected)/) - Protected routes requiring authentication
- [src/app/api/](mdc:src/app/api) - API routes
- [src/app/providers/](mdc:src/app/providers) - Context providers and wrappers

### File Conventions
- `page.tsx` - Route pages (default export required)
- `layout.tsx` - Layout components (default export required)
- `loading.tsx` - Loading UI for Suspense boundaries
- `error.tsx` - Error UI for error boundaries
- `not-found.tsx` - 404 page UI
- `globals.css` - Global styles

## Layout and Pages

### Root Layout
The root layout in [src/app/layout.tsx](mdc:src/app/layout.tsx) should:
- Include necessary providers (Clerk, React Query, etc.)
- Define global metadata
- Include global styles
- Set up error boundaries

### Page Structure
```typescript
// src/app/example/page.tsx
import { Metadata } from 'next';

export const metadata: Metadata = {
  title: 'Page Title',
  description: 'Page description',
};

export default function ExamplePage() {
  return (
    <div>
      {/* Page content */}
    </div>
  );
}
```

## Data Fetching

### Server Components
- Use Server Components by default for data fetching
- Fetch data directly in Server Components
- Use `async/await` for data fetching
- Cache data appropriately

### Client Components
- Use Client Components only when necessary (interactivity, hooks, browser APIs)
- Mark with `'use client'` directive
- Use React Query for client-side data fetching
- Handle loading and error states

### API Routes
- Place API routes in [src/app/api/](mdc:src/app/api)
- Use Route Handlers for API endpoints
- Return proper HTTP status codes
- Handle errors gracefully

## Authentication

### Clerk Integration
- Use Clerk for authentication
- Protect routes with middleware
- Handle authentication state in components
- Use Clerk hooks for user data

### Protected Routes
- Group protected routes in [src/app/(protected)/](mdc:src/app/(protected)/)
- Use middleware for route protection
- Handle authentication redirects
- Provide fallback UI for unauthenticated users

## Styling

### Global Styles
- Define global styles in [src/app/globals.css](mdc:src/app/globals.css)
- Import Tailwind CSS directives
- Define CSS custom properties
- Set up base styles

### Component Styling
- Use Tailwind CSS for component styling
- Create reusable component patterns
- Use CSS modules for complex styles
- Follow design system guidelines

## Performance

### Image Optimization
- Use Next.js Image component for optimized images
- Configure image domains in [next.config.ts](mdc:next.config.ts)
- Use appropriate image formats
- Implement lazy loading

### Font Optimization
- Use Next.js font optimization
- Load fonts efficiently
- Preload critical fonts
- Use font display swap

### Bundle Optimization
- Use dynamic imports for code splitting
- Optimize bundle size
- Use tree shaking effectively
- Monitor bundle analysis

## Configuration

### Next.js Config
The [next.config.ts](mdc:next.config.ts) should include:
- Image domain configuration
- Environment variables
- Build optimizations
- Custom webpack configuration if needed

### Environment Variables
- Use `.env.local` for local development
- Use `.env.production` for production
- Prefix with `NEXT_PUBLIC_` for client-side access
- Validate environment variables

## Error Handling

### Error Boundaries
- Implement error boundaries for route segments
- Provide meaningful error messages
- Log errors appropriately
- Handle different error types

### Loading States
- Use Suspense boundaries for loading states
- Provide skeleton UI
- Handle loading errors
- Optimize loading performance

## SEO and Metadata

### Metadata API
- Use Next.js Metadata API
- Define dynamic metadata
- Include Open Graph tags
- Set up structured data

### Dynamic Metadata
```typescript
export async function generateMetadata({ params }: Props): Promise<Metadata> {
  return {
    title: 'Dynamic Title',
    description: 'Dynamic description',
  };
}
```

## Middleware

### Authentication Middleware
- Use middleware for route protection
- Handle authentication redirects
- Set up proper headers
- Optimize middleware performance

### Custom Middleware
- Place in [src/middleware.ts](mdc:src/middleware.ts)
- Handle authentication logic
- Set up response headers
- Implement rate limiting if needed
